(105, 'Tand-Em', '200 OK', 677, 'http://www.oldskool.org/pc/tand-em/', NULL, NULL, 'Tand-Em is a Tandy 1000 and IBM PCjr emulator for 80386 (or higher)-based PCs. The PCjr and Tandy 1000 were PCs that had enhanced graphics and sound well before EGA or Adlib came out, and due to the Tandy''s popularity in the states, many games were programmed to take advantage of those enhanced graphics and sound.', 'Emulation', 'Spectrum', NULL, 0, '2002-02-12 00:00:00', 0),
